column5: This is an interesting educational online fishing show that Marc Thorpe does. The October episode came out yesterday. It's a 35 minute show so, get yasseff a coffee and enjoy.  http://www.fishfactor.tv/show.html
good video! I would love to one day go out for musky, and that was a very informative video on the handling/releasing of fish.
Thanks Mark for another informative video.   Art
Tks Roy and Art,in hopes the education and issues fish face at times serves as a value of better handling  be good  marc
Thank you Roy for posting this up and to you Marc and Carl , i enjoyed that .............Ron .
I've never heard of or caught a musky with "swim bladder issues" - strange.  I liked the video, good release techniques.
Finally had a chance to watch the whole thing, great video
yes marc knows his stuff,he has alot of his info on facebook and has lots of info,i have been reading and watching his vids for a few years,and he can sure catch the big muskies too !!!
Tks for the comments,the purpose of the show is to help acquire knowledge about various species,In this case the handling and issues muskies face  be good  marc

I must be missing something. The video I just watched was great, I enjoyed it, but there were no muskies involved. How do I get to the musky vid?  Anyways, the gill netting video was great. Very interesting, indeed. Keep them coming. I enjoy this type of thing over an actual fishing show any day.  Good stuff, Marc. Keep them coming!  S.
Same here, Great video.  I love that type of stuff.
Sorry about that its was the Oct show and was in the archives. We air one once a month around 15 to 20 of each month  Here is the muskies show  Muskie
Thanks, I found the archives and watched the other videos as well. Great job. I will continue to follow these. Much better than the standard "fishing shows" on Tv.  S.
